# Frontend Architect Standards

## TypeScript
- Strict mode always. No `any`; use `unknown` with type guards if needed.
- Explicit types for public APIs, hooks, and component props.
- Domain types in `types/` or `@shared`.

## RTL & Arabic
- RTL is default. Use logical properties: `ps`, `pe`, `ms`, `me`, `start`, `end`.
- Never use `left`, `right`, `ml-`, `mr-` for layout — use `ms-`, `me-`, `inset-inline-*`.
- Arabic typography: Tajawal, IBM Plex Arabic, Cairo.

## Tailwind & Styling
- Design tokens from `platform-theme.ts`, `icon-styles.ts`. No arbitrary values without tokens.
- No inline styles. No duplicated utility patterns.

## Components
- shadcn/ui for all platform and admin pages. Re-author for RTL correctness.
- Feature isolation. Predictable imports. No circular dependencies.

## Change Logging
- Document meaningful changes in `frontend-change-log.md`: What, Why, Impact, Trade-offs.
